reviewText: i am very happy with this order, i love these videos and the price could not have been better, very satisfied
I bought this dvd because I thought it would be a great workout, I have not tried it yet to busy
My husband wanted a tae bo dvd that was easy for him to follow, and gave him a good workout in a short amount of time. This dvd was just what he was looking for!
This is classic Tae Bo. Has all the moves you know and love. Not as intense as I'm used to but good. Shipping was good and prompt

Basically, the 2 circuit DVD's are well structured and pleasant workouts, not too easy and not too tough. Consider Circuit 1 as a basic DVD, Circuit 2 as an advanced DVD - the main difference is that it lasts longer and is set at a higher pace. Definitely good value for money, and together with the original advanced and the Tae Bo 2 Get Ripped Advanced my favourite Tae Bo workouts.
I have had issues losing weight for a long time..but these tapes have showed a definite weight loss, stamina improvement and overall healthier feeling.

These two workouts were a great disappointment.  Having enjoyed the workouts of the original Tae bo tapes I was looking for a updated version but found with the Circuit workouts I barely broke a sweat, was bored and wanted my money back.

I have been doing the Tae Bo workouts by Billy Blanks for the last couple years now and love them. The newest DVD's - Tae Bo Circuit 1 & 2 are similar to the original Advanced Tae Bo tape in that they are very fast paced but easy to follow and enjoyable. The workouts are quick paced and are not boring like sitting on an excersise bike. I highly recommend these to someone looking for an advanced cardio workout with strength training and toning that doesn't have a lot of time to workout, average DVD is about 40 minutes.
